= POM

* http://proutils.rubyforge.org
* http://protuils.rubyforge.org/pom


== DESCRIPTION

Ruby POM stands for Ruby Project Object Model.
POM provides a metata system for Ruby projects.


== FEATURES/ISSUES

* Standardizes common project metadata.
* Uses meta directory files for properties.


== RELEASE NOTES

Please see HISTORY file.


== SYNOPSIS

Usage is fairly straight forward. Simply create a Pom::Metadata object
passing the constructor the root directory of the project.

  metadata = Pom::Metadata.new(rootdir)

Then you can query information from the project via method calls.

  metadata.package  #=> 'mayapp'

Look as the Metadata class to see what specific information is supported.


== HOW TO INSTALL

To install with RubyGems simply open a console and type:

  gem install pom

Local installation requires Setup.rb (gem install setup),
then download the tarball package and type:

  tar -xvzf pom-1.0.0.tgz
  cd pom-1.0.0.tgz
  sudo setup.rb all

Windows users use 'ruby setup.rb all'.


